# Copy to `.env` (same directory) and fill in. `.env` is gitignored and must STAY
# gitignored: this repo is handed to judges, and a key committed once lives in the
# git history forever, even after the file is deleted. GitHub's secret scanning will
# also flag it and Google may auto-revoke the key -- possibly mid-demo.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      # then paste your key below
#
# Optional in every sense: with no key the analyzer falls back to rules, loudly and
# instantly. Rules is the deterministic, rehearsed path and the one to demo on.

GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Optional. Leave unset to use the default in analyzer/gemini.py.
#
# Pick a model by MEASURING it against two constraints, not by picking the biggest:
#
#   latency < TIMEOUT_S (10s). A model slower than the timeout does not fail
#   loudly -- it silently becomes a rules run wearing a gemini badge. Measured on
#   this prompt: gemini-3.1-flash-lite 1.0s, gemini-flash-latest 15.6s (times out),
#   gemini-3.5-flash 18.7s (times out).
#
#   RPD headroom. Free-tier quota is per-project-PER-MODEL, and one demo run costs
#   one call. gemini-3.1-flash-lite has 500 RPD / 15 RPM; 2.5-flash, 3-flash and
#   3.5-flash have 20 RPD -- which does not survive a rehearsal day plus the demo.
#
# The `gemini-flash-latest` alias dodges 404s on newer projects, but it silently
# repoints, which is the one thing you do not want between rehearsal and demo.
# If a pinned id 404s or 429s, the analyzer names the model and status code, then
# falls back to rules.
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3.1-flash-lite
